The paper focuses on developing an approach for human-to-robot handovers, which is a critical capability for collaborative robots. The proposed approach involves collecting a human grasp dataset and learning a deep model to classify the hand grasps into different categories. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves computer vision techniques for detecting the human grasp and planning trajectories accordingly, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves human-computer interaction and usability studies, which suggests that it could belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The use of deep learning models for grasp classification suggests that the paper could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
